title: Terms of trade in goods
maintainer_displayname: ZBO | Centraal Bureau voor de Statistiek
name: terms-of-trade-in-goods
notes:
Statistics Netherlands collects monthly data on imports and exports of goods. This table comprises index figures and changes in terms of percentage of terms of trade, import price and export price of goods. Imports and exports are defined by change in economic ownership of the goods concerned. The indices are based on 2010=100. The changes in terms of percentage are compared with the same period twelve months previously.

Data available from: January 2001.

Status of the figures:
Figures for 2011 are definite. Figures for 2012 are revised provisional, figures for 2013, 2014 and 2015 are provisional. The figures for the period 2001-2010 are still provisional as the revision of the National Accounts has not yet been completed for the accounting period before 2011. Among other things, this revision comprises the introduction of accounting rules of the ESA 2010 in the National Accounts. 

Changes as of 16 March 2015:
Data on January 2015 have been added. Data on October until December, the fourth quarter and year 2014 have been adjusted.

Terms of trade figures may be adjusted once new or updated source information becomes available on the monthly international trade statistics or producers' prices. In addition, monthly price changes are adjusted retrospectively to fit those of imports and exports of goods in the Quarterly national accounts.

When will new figures be published?
About six to seven weeks after the end of the month under review.
